cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF 

This paper deals with improving the performance of WiFi networks, specifically addressing issues related to network congestion and queueing. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and could also be considered under the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SY) as the paper proposes a new queueing scheme and scheduler. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a theoretical model and experiments, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) and performance analysis (cs.PF).
